During a press briefing, White House Press Secretary Sarah Sanders provided updates on the administration's efforts to support the recovery and relief efforts in the aftermath of Hurricane Harvey. Sanders mentioned that Vice President Mike Pence and five Cabinet secretaries are in Texas meeting with local officials and storm survivors. She also stated that President Trump plans to donate $1 million of his personal money to hurricane relief efforts. Additionally, Sanders addressed questions about the administration's stance on DACA, stating that a final decision has not been made and that the President's priority is helping all Americans, including middle-class citizens. Sanders also mentioned that the President will be traveling to Texas and Louisiana on Saturday to assess the situation firsthand.